recipes.title: Subaru Impreza WRX STI(GC8) version 1 1994
recipes.description:
The first generation (GC8) of the legendary Subaru Impreza WRX Sti was launched way back in 1994, offered in saloon (GC8).
The Gen 1 STi, all powered by the famous 2.0 litre turbo motor, but producing from 247 bhp in the first version

recipes.title: Subaru Impreza WRX STI(GC8) version 2 1995
recipes.description: This car has a 4 door saloon (sedan) type body with a front positioned engine driving through all four wheels. It is powered by a turbocharged engine of 2 litre capacity. This unit features double overhead camshaft valve gear, 4 cylinder layout, and 4 valves per cylinder. It develops 271 bhp (275 PS/202 kW) of power at 6500 rpm, and maximum torque of 319 N·m (235 lb·ft/32.5 kgm) at 4000 rpm. A 5 speed manual gearbox delivers the power to the wheels. The Subaru Impreza WRX STi Version II weighs a claimed 1240 kg at the kerb.

recipes.title: Subaru Impreza WRX STI(GC8) version 3 1996
recipes.description: The Impreza WRX STi Version III is an all wheel drive saloon car with a front located engine, sold by Subaru. It forms part of Subaru's GC8 series of cars. It's powered courtesy of a turbocharged engine of 2 litre capacity. This unit features double overhead camshaft valve gear, 4 cylinder layout, and 4 valves per cylinder. It has an output of 276 bhp (280 PS/206 kW) of power at 6500 rpm, and maximum torque of 343 N·m (253 lb·ft/35 kgm) at 4000 rpm. Power is supplied to the wheels via a 5 speed manual transmission. The Subaru Impreza WRX STi Version III weighs a stated 1250 kg at the kerb.

recipes.title: Subaru Impreza WRX STI(GC8) 22B STI version 1998
recipes.description: Subaru Impreza 22B STi is an automobile that has a 2 door coupé type body with a front positioned engine driving through all four wheels. It is powered by a turbocharged engine of 2.2 litre capacity. This unit features double overhead camshaft valve gear, 4 cylinder layout, and 4 valves per cylinder. It produces 276 bhp (280 PS/206 kW) of power at 6000 rpm, and maximum torque of 363 N·m (268 lb·ft/37 kgm) at 3200 rpm. The power is delivered to the wheels by means of a 5 speed manual gearbox. The Subaru Impreza 22B STi weighs a quoted 1270 kg at the kerb. It is claimed to achieve a top speed of 248 km/h (154 mph).
